name: Rumalogy Coffee & Kitchen
address: Jl. Sinta Jl. Raya Tugu Pahlawan No.mor 52, Bitera, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: The food is relaitively cheap, taste is good but not that good, coffee‚Ä¶idk why the branch in Ari Canti Hospital serve more yumy coffee than this branch. All the waitresses are so kind, ambience is good, esp when they switched their playlist from loud music to the calmer tunes. It‚Äôs already good but there‚Äôs always room for improvement.
review 2: I can't say this place is fancy, yet it has place in my heart (& mind). I didn't expect that I'd find place like this in Gianyar area (I live in Denpasar, so I have no idea about this). Small place, yet they can make everything looks comfy & cozy. The food is affordable & tasty, the music they choose uplift the mood (some places sometimes choose sad music/sad song/ballad for a cafe, not really a thing for me. Staffs are very nice too. If I may give just one suggestion for the owner & staff, maybe you can remove the plastics (small containers for sauces, straw) and use something else for substitute. Overall, I recommend this place for people who want to enjoy their afternoon break.
review 3: Ordered twice. Turned my belly inside out twice. Cannot recommend at all.
review 4: small portion and not expensive but the taste is pricelessü•∫‚ú®üí´
review 5: I order take out from Gojek, cost around 80,000 IDR. The food tastes just ok, but the portion is so small.
